==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: turacou
<hw>tu*ra"cou</hw></mhw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F. <ets>touraco</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Any one of several species of large brightly crested birds of the
genus <gen>Turacus</gen>, native of Africa. They eat plantain and are
remarkable for the peculiar green and red pigments found in their
feathers.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>touraco</asp>,
<asp>touracou</asp>, and <asp>turakoo</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

